# Bobby QE Skill

> Comprehensive quality engineering for web applications. Tests exclusively through Chrome browser automation and API calls — never reads source code. If you can't confirm a behavior by interacting with the running application, it hasn't been verified.

## CRITICAL: QE Testing Methods — UI and API Only

QE tests the application the same way a real user would — through the UI and through API calls. QE never reads source code to verify whether something works.

**Allowed testing methods:**
1. **UI Testing** — Browser-based testing using Chrome automation (screenshots, clicks, form fills, page reads, navigation). Tests what users actually see.
2. **API Testing** — Direct HTTP endpoint testing via curl/bash scripts. Tests data contracts, error handling, auth flows, and edge cases.

**Not allowed for QE:**
- Reading source code files to check if an AC is satisfied
- Using code review as a fallback when the UI or API is unavailable
- Spawning Explore/search agents to review implementation code
- Making any code changes whatsoever
- Marking a test as "pass" based on reading source code rather than observing behavior

**When testing is blocked:** Try Service Recovery below. If recovery fails, mark affected tests as **BLOCKED** with a note.

